# Nukoder Design System & Mobile App Walkthrough

I have successfully consolidated the design system into a unified library and built a multi-screen mobile application prototype to showcase the components in action.

## Key Accomplishments

### 1. Unified Design System (`src/Nukoder_DS`)
The design system is now isolated in its own folder, providing a single source of truth for:
- **Tokens:** Comprehensive dark and light theme definitions.
- **Primitives:** Shared components like [Ico](file:///Users/Adedayo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/ds-preview/src/Nukoder_DS/index.jsx#86-94), [Badge](file:///Users/Adedayo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/ds-preview/src/Nukoder_DS/index.jsx#95-109), [Av](file:///Users/Adedayo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/ds-preview/src/Nukoder_DS/index.jsx#110-124) (Avatar), and [IBox](file:///Users/Adedayo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/ds-preview/src/Nukoder_DS/index.jsx#125-136).
- **Theme Provider:** A React context that manages global theme state.

### 2. Mobile App Prototype ([src/Nukodes_App.jsx](file:///Users/Adedayo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/ds-preview/src/Nukodes_App.jsx))
A high-fidelity mobile prototype featuring:
- **Phone Frame:** A premium container representing a modern mobile device.
- **5 Core Screens:** Dashboard, Products, Invoices, Customers, and Settings.
- **Bottom Navigation:** A smooth tab bar for switching between sections.
- **Theme Support:** Global light/dark mode toggle accessible from Settings.

### 3. Application Selector ([src/main.jsx](file:///Users/Adedayo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/ds-preview/src/main.jsx))
A non-destructive entry point that allows you to toggle between the **DS Reference** and the **Mobile App**.

